		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">True Paladins<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, May 5th 5:00 PM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10837908188092&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10837908188092&num=3&post=1&replyto=10837908188092"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10837908188092></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=317742"><span id=>Bairie</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>3 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Bairie&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Props to Veludeus and a big thumbs-down to Ralston. As the proud owner of both a 65 much-requested pally and ENC, I know for a fact that if you don't use stuns, I don't want you anywhere near my group. I've been on both ends.<br><br>First off, realize what a Paladin is before you ever start one... DEFENSE. Get that in your head immediately. Paladins are all about sacrifice. Your job is to take a beating so everyone else can drop the mob. Your role is to do everything you possibly can to avoid letting anyone else get hit. Get that in your head and you'll truly understand the character and why it's loved by others.<br><br>Pallys are truly a class that gets better as they get higher, the way it should be. At low levels, Root is a life-saver, but those little stuns gain agro nicely at little cost of mana. I used Cease and Desist up to lvl 60 because it cost nothing to cast and ticks off mobs, whether it stuns them or not.<br><br>By PoP, HPs (and STA obviously) are imperative. Procs, out-damaging others, that don't mean JACK! Once the pull is in, You stun that puppy not once, but twice. When I group, my slower can slow a mob, clerics toss HoT on me, before it ever reaches us... Because they KNOW that they aren't going to be touched the entire fight.<br><br>I will Stun, Root, kick, bite, scratch eyeballs, steal tires.. whatever it takes to keep a mob from touching my casters. It's pitifully easy.. stun, count to 2, stun, and yaulp... rinse, repeat. Taunting along constantly, of course.<br><br>A stun or two every 45 seconds or so is enough that your casters will be medding thru the fight giving tells to each other about how much they love this paladin.<br><br>In fact, I won't even join a group with my Enchanter if they don't have a good Paladin. I don't waste my time.<br><br>SKs, adequate... WARs, please don't make me laugh. For agro, you want one thing and one thing only... a Paladin.<br><br>One other reason to stun... Sure, you will never have the HPs of a WAR. So what? Chain-stuns not only keep agro, but save tremendously-valuable cleric mana. There's about 30 seconds per fight that a Paladin never gets hit. It's like having more HPs. Less cleric medding = more XP for all.<br><br>PS - Stuns wasting swings? Bud, you aren't the DMG-dealer and you NEVER will be. Pallys put in slow, meaty, juicy 2H swings. And notice that AFTER your casting is complete, the swings you that would have taken during the cast are instantly taken. That was patched over 2 years ago. You don't &quot;miss&quot; any swings at the mob, your weapon delay is replaced by the casting time.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>*Bairie Manalow* 65 Bard<br>Tunare's Finest!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, May 5th 6:20 PM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10837908188092&num=3&post=1&replyto=10837956009908"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10837956009908></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=133177"><span id=Scholar>Ralston</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>272 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Ralston&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>The issue being addressed was CHAIN stunning, not the 2 stuns every 45 seconds that gets me love notes from my casters.. Beleieve me. I take it personally if my casters take hits unneccesarily. And I get plenty of offers to tank for groups. I'm on a lot of friend lists. :)<br><br>My intention wasn't to dissuade people from stunning. It's a valuable tool in the Pally toolbox, for sure. And I use it. I stun as a puller brings a mob in, and when those big nukes and backstabs start landing.<br><br>I've n-e-v-e-r found it necessary to chain stun mobs to hold aggro. I know very well what a Paladin's job is and couldn't agree with you more.<br><br>But If I only have to stun a mob a couple times every 45 seconds, why should I have 6 stun spells loaded up and chain casting instead of adding to the overall DPS?<br><br>Or is 2 stuns every 45 seconds considered chain stunning? In which case, you have my most sincere apologies. Chain stunning is imperative.<br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May&nbsp;&nbsp;5 18:58:15 2004</em></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Ralston Purina<br>Mith Marr Lord Protector<br>Prexus Server<br><br>"So many Undead. So Little Time"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
